-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Tool      : sdRNAprofiles
Version   : v1.0
Summary   : A tool for the de-novo discovery of small RNAs and derived RNA molecules, from small RNA-Seq data

Usage     : sdrnaprofiles [OPTIONS] <srnaseq.bam> <output_folder>

Output    : sdrnaprofiles will generate three files in the output_folder directory:
            - output_folder/profiles.dat
            - output_folder/crosscor.dat
            - output_folder/clusters.dat

Options   :
           -x     Minimum correlation
                  Threshold for the cross-correlation value of the same contig between different replicates.
                  Must be between [0,1].
                  - Default is 0.99

           -m     Minimum length
                  Minimum length required to report a contig.
                  Must be > 5.
                  - Default is 15

           -M     Maximum length
                  Maximum length required to report a contig.
                  Must be > 6.
                  If -m option is present, maximum length must be greater than minimum length.
                  - Default is 200

           -s     Spacing
                  Maximum space required between two reads to be considered part of the same contig.
                  Must be 0 or a positive number
                  - Default is 20

           -r     Minimum number of reads
                  Minimum number of reads required to report a contig.
                  Must be 0 or a positive number.
                  - Default is 10

           -t     Trimming threshold
                  Trim nucleotides in the 5'- and 3'-ends of the contig that have -t reads or less
                  Must be 0 or a positive number
                  - Default is 2
                  
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Tool      : plotprofiles
Version   : v1.0
Summary   : A tool to draw sRNA profiles discovered using the sdrnaprofiles tool

Usage     : plotprofiles [OPTIONS] <profiles.dat> <profile_name_1> [<profile_name_2> ... <profile_name_n>]

Output    : plotprofiles will open a X11 window displaying the profile or will generate a png file

Options   :
           -o    PNG file.
                 The plot will be printed in the specified PNG file.
                 - Default behaviour is to open the plot in a system window
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
